{"key":"processedPost-7129248","value":{"id":7129248,"first":7125243,"last":7147280,"when":1183588418,"utime":"07/05/07 01:33 AM","content":"Those jars are way too full, and with the tyvek under the lid, it will get damp and thus allow bacterial contaminants to colonize right under the filter.  You'll end up with a much higher rate of failure that way than using regular mason jars with the filter on the outside of the lid.<br />You don't want your jars more than 3/4 full in order to allow shaking room.  2/3 full is better.<br />RR","title":"Re: Colonization of rye issue"}}